  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will build a children&#x2019;s therapy garden at an inner-city foster home in Chicago that cares for abused, neglected and abandoned kids.  From a toddler left in an apartment for two weeks to a teenager that was chained to his basement wall, we have found that many of the children begin to heal when caring for something smaller and more vulnerable than themselves.</narrative>
